# Subagent delegation

When the PO lists **multiple separate issues or tasks**, the coordinating agent MUST spawn **one subagent per issue**. One subagent MUST NOT handle multiple PO-listed items.

## Coordinator duties

0. **Scope gate** — open or claim a GitHub issue for each PO-listed unit before delegation.
1. Decompose the PO request into independent issues (or confirm one issue).
2. Launch parallel subagents when work is independent; serialize API-first when HTTP/OpenAPI is shared.
3. Serialize or split paths when subagents would edit the same files.
4. Synthesize work subagent results into a single PO-facing summary (outcomes, blockers, next steps).
5. **Integration verification** — re-run applicable quality gates on the combined merged tree.
6. **Security review** — when MUST triggers apply, run `security-review` on combined diff before ship.
7. Apply partial-ship rules; spawn one ship subagent (ce-commit-push-pr); **MUST NOT** commit, push, or open PR directly when work subagents were spawned.
8. **CI watch** — ship subagent owns loop-on-ci after push; coordinator MAY own if ship subagent cannot loop.
9. Register gaps as GitHub issues per [issue-registration](issue-registration.mdc); do not expand slice scope.

Full protocol: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md#issue-registration).

## Partial ship

| Situation | Ship subagent |
| --- | --- |
| All PO-listed work subagents done | MUST spawn |
| Blocked on PO decision, secrets, or irreversible choice for PO-listed item | MUST NOT spawn |
| Optional item deferred; blocked work filed as debt and removed from slice AC | MAY spawn for completed items |

## Work subagent duties

- Own exactly **one** PO-listed issue end to end.
- Run applicable quality gates before reporting done.
- Return structured done (verification evidence, files changed) or blockers (tried, failed, needed decision/access) — not open-ended questions.
- MUST NOT commit, push, or open PRs when a coordinator is active.

## Ship subagent duties

- Spawned once by the coordinator after integration verify and security review (when triggered).
- MUST commit, push, and open or update a single PR for the combined slice diff.
- Owns fix-ci / loop-on-ci after push until checks pass or blocked.

## Example

PO: "Fix login bug and add export button."

- Subagent 1 → login bug only
- Subagent 2 → export button only
- Coordinator → scope gate → parallel launch → synthesize → integration verify → ship subagent → CI watch

## Anti-patterns

- One subagent doing both login and export when PO listed them separately
- Each work subagent opening its own PR or pushing independently
- Coordinator committing, pushing, or opening PR when work subagents were spawned
- Coordinator implementing code while subagents are active on the same issue
- Skipping integration verification on combined subagent diffs
- Asking PO to pick implementation details that do not affect product behavior
